name: tetrahydroxysuccinic acid
Reason: 1,3,4-thiadiazole ring formation introduces additional rigid structures that can participate in dipole interactions and potentially hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by about +70°C. The presence of four methoxy groups can also contribute to an increase in molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, with an approximate increase of +20°C per group, totaling +80°C. The carbonyl group introduces polar carbonyl interactions, contributing approximately +40°C.
